cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with relation extraction from biomedical literature using Named-Entity Recognition tools. It also involves the use of deep learning tools, which are commonly used in natural language processing. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because of the use of deep learning tools. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible sub-category because of the use of machine learning techniques to automatically recognize phenotype-gene relations. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is a possible sub-category because the paper deals with extracting information from biomedical literature. 

Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is a possible sub-category because of the use of deep learning tools.
